<FILEID>AP-NR-09-23-89 0218EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r a AM-ElevatorExplosion     09-23 0174</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Elevator Explosion,0179</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two Killed, Three Hurt In Grain Elevator Blast</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BINGHAM LAKE, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A grain elevator explosion in this
southwestern Minnesota town Friday killed two people and injured
three others, authorities said.
   The bodies of two employees of Cargill Inc., which owns the
elevator, were recovered about two hours after the 2:30 p.m.
explosion, said to a dispatcher for the Cottonwood County Sheriff's
Department.
   The dead were identified as John William Gahler, 39, and Leonard
Dunkelberger, 51, both of Bingham Lake.
   Rescue workers had to empty the 75,000-bushel bin to recover the
bodies, the sheriff's department said.
   Three people were hospitalized at Windom Hospital with minor
injuries suffered in the explosion, said nursing supervisor Carla
Mitchell. All three were in stable condition and remained under
observation Friday night, she said.
   The cause of the explosion was not immediately known, Cargill
spokesman Garland West said. He said there was no fire, although
some materials were smoldering after the explosion.
   The sheriff's department said the entire elevator complex
sustained extensive structural damage.
</TEXT>
