<FIRST>r a PM-NudeBatherSlain     09-23 0185</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Nude Bather Slain,0192</SECOND>
<HEAD>Sunbather Slain as Wife Looks On</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTA BARBARA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A nude sunbather was gunned down at
a secluded beach by an attacker demanding drugs, jolting this sleepy
tourist area where random violence is rare.
   Phillip Bogdanoff, 49, was lying on a beach blanket with his wife
Thursday afternoon when two men approached the couple and demanded
marijuana, Santa Barbara County sheriff's Sgt. Jan Bullard said.
   When Bogdanoff said he had none, one of the men shot him twice in
the head, killing him, Ms. Bullard said.
   Both men fled and remain at large, police said. Bogdanoff's wife,
Diana, 41, was not attacked.
   Nudity did not appear to figure as a motive in the killing, Ms.
Bullard said.
   ``There were no sexual overtones,'' she said. ``Nothing more to
it. Just a random, violent act.''
   The slaying at the beach about 20 miles up the coast from this
seaside city, which is 75 miles northwest of Los Angeles, alarmed
residents.
   ``We don't expect this kind of thing to happen around here,'' Ms.
Bullard said. ``It woke up a sleepy county.''
</TEXT>
