<HEAD>President Lauds Composer</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush said Saturday that composer Irvin
Berlin, was ``a legendary man whose words and music will help define
the history of our nation.''
   Just minutes before Bush's statement was released, the president
joined a crowd of thousands to sing ``God Bless America,'' one of
the many songs written by Berlin. The occasion was a luncheon of
Roman Catholic lawyers where Bush spoke.
   ``Very few people have come to touch and move the soul of a
nation, reflecting its spirit and traditions,'' Bush said of Berlin,
