<SECOND>AM-Peru-Rebels,0125</SECOND>
<HEAD>Armed Rebels Raid News Offices in Lima</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LIMA, Peru (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Armed leftist rebels forced their way into the
offices of two foreign news services in Lima Saturday and made
staff members transmit statements, according to employees at the
agencies.
   Members of the pro-Cuban Tupac Amaru Revolutionary Movement
raided the offices of Agence-France Presse, a French news agency,
and United Press International, an American wire service.
   No one was injured in either incident.
   Employees of both agencies said three rebels with pistols took
over each office Saturday morning, painted slogans on the walls,
ordered that statements be transmitted and then left.
   The communiques criticized the International Monetary Fund,
which has been negotiating with Peru on its loan payments.
